.\" Man page for appicon
.TH APPICON 1 "July 2026" "appicon" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
appicon \- resolve desktop and brand icons to local file paths
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B appicon
\fIcommand\fR [\fIoptions\fR] [\fIargs\fR...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B appicon
looks up an application or brand icon and prints a local filesystem path.
Consumers such as Waybar, Rofi, and scripts can use the path without embedding
remote download logic.
.PP
Default resolve order: file, overrides, FreeDesktop icon theme / .desktop
(including Flatpak/Snap heuristics on Linux, and Steam heuristics), then SVGL.
Customize the full pipeline (opt\-in CDN/github/BYOK/glyph stages and local packs)
via sources.json or sources.yaml. A miss exits with status 1 unless a glyph stage
is reached. The optional unix\-socket daemon is supported on Unix; Windows uses
in\-process resolve only.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B resolve [\-\-json] [\-\-explain] [\-\-offline] [\-\-local] [\-\-order \fITYPES\fR] [\-\-format svg|png] [\-\-size N] [\-\-theme dark|light] \fIquery\fR...
Resolve one or more queries and print absolute paths (or JSON with \-\-json).
Multiple queries emit {results:[…]} with \-\-json.
\-\-order is a comma-separated list of stage types.
\-\-explain includes tried stages and a miss hint (auth\-skipped BYOK stages appear as
stage(auth)).
When a daemon socket is present, dial it unless \-\-local or APPICON_NO_DAEMON is set
(order, explain, batch, and prefetch are supported over the socket).
.TP
.B prefetch [\-\-json] [\-\-offline] [\-\-from\-desktop] [\-\-theme dark|light] [\-\-order \fITYPES\fR] [\fIquery\fR...]
Warm the cache for queries (same effective order as resolve).
\-\-from\-desktop derives queries from installed .desktop files.
Uses the daemon socket when available (same as resolve).
.TP
.B status [\-\-json]
Print config/cache/pack paths, effective order, BYOK credentials readiness,
platform (goos/goarch), daemon socket support, and helper tools.
.TP
.B cache path|clear|stats|prune
Inspect or manage the on-disk cache under $XDG_CACHE_HOME/appicon
(or the platform cache dir when XDG_CACHE_HOME is unset).
.TP
.B override list|get|set|rm|path|suggest|export|import [\-\-json]
Manage overrides.json / overrides.yaml query remaps (long-tail aliases).
.B suggest
proposes remap targets; \-\-from\-misses uses recent miss queries.
.B export
/
.B import
bulk dump or load JSON/YAML (\-\-format, \-\-file, \-\-merge).
.TP
.B sources list|get|set|path [\-\-json] [\-\-file \fIPATH\fR] [\-\-format json|yaml]
Show effective order, read/write sources.json|yaml, or print its path.
.B set
reads JSON/YAML from stdin or \-\-file.
.TP
.B pack list|path|add|install|update [\-\-json] ...
Manage local icon packs (add directory, install recipes or git/.tar.gz URLs,
update clones, or install from \-\-from-bundle).
.TP
.B daemon [\-\-socket \fIpath\fR]
Run the optional unix-socket resolve daemon (or under systemd socket activation).
Refused on Windows (use in\-process resolve).
.TP
.B mcp
Run a stdio MCP server for coding agents (tools: resolve, prefetch, status,
sources_*, pack_*, override_* including export/import, cache_*, version). Prefer MCP
tools over shelling the CLI when connected.
.TP
.B completion bash|zsh|fish
Print a shell completion script to stdout.
.TP
.B man
Print this man page (troff) to stdout.
.TP
.B version
Print the version string.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Resolve an app icon:
.B appicon resolve firefox
.TP
JSON PNG for a panel:
.B appicon resolve \-\-json \-\-format png \-\-size 24 "VS Code"
.TP
Warm cache then offline resolve:
.B appicon prefetch firefox discord
.br
.B appicon resolve \-\-offline firefox
.TP
Install a local pack and remap a WM class:
.B appicon pack install simple-icons
.br
.B appicon override set my\-wm\-class firefox
.TP
BYOK Logo.dev (token in env, never in config):
.B export LOGO_DEV_TOKEN=pk_…
.br
.B appicon resolve \-\-order logo\-dev,xdg shopify.com
.TP
Bulk overrides:
.B appicon override export \-\-format yaml > overrides.yaml
.br
.B appicon override import \-\-merge \-\-file overrides.yaml
.TP
Inspect environment:
.B appicon status
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B XDG_CACHE_HOME
Cache root parent (default ~/.cache; on Windows, UserCacheDir when unset).
Assets live in $XDG_CACHE_HOME/appicon.
.TP
.B XDG_CONFIG_HOME
Config parent (default ~/.config; on Windows, UserConfigDir when unset).
Reads appicon/overrides.json|yaml and sources.json|yaml.
.TP
.B XDG_DATA_HOME
Data parent (default ~/.local/share; on Windows, LOCALAPPDATA when unset).
Packs default under appicon/packs/.
.TP
.B XDG_DATA_DIRS / XDG_RUNTIME_DIR
FreeDesktop roots (Linux defaults for /usr share and Flatpak/Snap).
Daemon socket defaults to $XDG_RUNTIME_DIR/appicon.sock, else a private
cache\-backed run dir.
.TP
.B APPICON_THEME
Default dark|light preference when \-\-theme is omitted.
.TP
.B APPICON_ICON_THEME
Override FreeDesktop icon theme name.
.TP
.B APPICON_SOCKET
Override daemon socket path (default $XDG_RUNTIME_DIR/appicon.sock).
.TP
.B APPICON_NO_DAEMON
When set, resolve never dials the daemon socket.
.TP
.B APPICON_OFFLINE
When set, skip network (same as resolve \-\-offline); pack install/update refuse.
.TP
.I token_env / secret_env names
BYOK stages reference env var
.I names
in sources config (e.g. LOGO_DEV_TOKEN). Values must be secrets, never file paths.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/appicon/overrides.json
Query remaps (e.g. WM class to catalog name). YAML alternate: overrides.yaml.
.TP
.I $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/appicon/sources.json
Ordered resolve stages (file, overrides, xdg, pack, svgl, opt\-in remotes including
logo\-dev / iconify / noun\-project, glyph). YAML alternate: sources.yaml.
.TP
.I $XDG_DATA_HOME/appicon/packs/
Recommended local pack root.
.TP
.I $XDG_CACHE_HOME/appicon/
Downloaded SVGs, CDN/github/BYOK assets, glyph SVGs, and rasterized PNGs.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
Not found (supported miss for consumers).
.TP
.B 2
Usage or configuration error.
.SH SEE ALSO
Project docs (when installing from source): docs/sources.md, docs/packs.md,
docs/consumer-contract.md, docs/resolve-result.schema.json.
Homepage: https://github.com/bolens/appicon
